# NADAZ Website — Cursor Rules
# PT. Arta Prima Glassindo | nadaz.co.id

## Project Identity
You are building a premium, awwwards-level one-page landing page for NADAZ,
a specialist glass & aluminum company in Jabodetabek, Indonesia.
All UI text is in Bahasa Indonesia.

---

## Tech Stack (Strict)
- Next.js 15 with App Router
- TypeScript (strict mode)
- Tailwind CSS v4
- shadcn/ui for base UI components
- GSAP 3 + ScrollTrigger + @gsap/react for ALL animations
- Lucide React for icons
- next/image for all images
- next/font for typography

Do NOT use:
- Framer Motion (use GSAP instead)
- Styled components or CSS modules
- Any other animation library
- Inline styles

---

## Brand & Design Rules

### Colors (use CSS variables)
```
bg-[--color-brand-dark]    → #0A1628  (main background)
bg-[--color-brand-navy]    → #0F1F3D  (card/surface background)
text-[--color-brand-white] → #E8EEF8  (primary text)
text-[--color-brand-muted] → #8899B3  (secondary text)
text-[--color-brand-gold]  → #C9A84C  (accent, headings, CTAs)
bg-[--color-brand-blue]    → #1B4F8A  (brand blue, buttons)
```

### Typography Classes
```
font-display  → Cormorant Garant (headings, display text)
font-sans     → DM Sans (body text, UI)
font-mono     → JetBrains Mono (labels, tags, captions)
```

### Glass Effect (use consistently)
```tsx
className="bg-[--color-glass-bg] backdrop-blur-md border border-[--color-glass-border] rounded-2xl"
```

---

## Component Patterns

### Section Template
Every section follows this pattern:
```tsx
"use client"
import { useRef } from "react"
import { useGSAP } from "@gsap/react"
import { gsap } from "gsap"
import { ScrollTrigger } from "gsap/ScrollTrigger"

export default function XxxSection() {
  const sectionRef = useRef<HTMLElement>(null)

  useGSAP(() => {
    // animations scoped to sectionRef
    gsap.fromTo(".reveal-item", 
      { opacity: 0, y: 40 },
      {
        opacity: 1, y: 0,
        stagger: 0.12,
        duration: 0.8,
        ease: "power3.out",
        scrollTrigger: {
          trigger: sectionRef.current,
          start: "top 80%",
        },
      }
    )
  }, { scope: sectionRef })

  return (
    <section id="[id]" ref={sectionRef} className="relative py-24 lg:py-32">
      {/* content */}
    </section>
  )
}
```

### Section Heading Pattern
```tsx
<div className="reveal-item">
  <span className="font-mono text-xs tracking-[0.3em] text-[--color-brand-gold] uppercase mb-4 block">
    {eyebrowText}
  </span>
  <h2 className="font-display text-4xl lg:text-6xl font-semibold text-[--color-brand-white] leading-tight">
    {title}
  </h2>
</div>
```

### CTA Button (Primary — WhatsApp)
```tsx
<a
  href="https://wa.me/6285328613613"
  target="_blank"
  rel="noopener noreferrer"
  className="inline-flex items-center gap-3 px-8 py-4 bg-[--color-brand-gold] text-[--color-brand-dark] font-sans font-semibold rounded-full hover:bg-[--color-brand-gold-light] transition-all duration-300 hover:scale-105 hover:shadow-[0_0_30px_rgba(201,168,76,0.3)]"
>
  <WhatsAppIcon />
  Konsultasi Gratis
</a>
```

---

## GSAP Animation Rules

1. **Register plugins ONCE** in `app/layout.tsx`, not in components
2. **Always scope** animations with `{ scope: sectionRef }`
3. **Always use** `@gsap/react`'s `useGSAP` hook, never `useEffect`
4. **Standard eases**: `power3.out` (reveals), `expo.out` (dramatic), `sine.inOut` (ambient)
5. **Stagger**: 0.08–0.15s for lists, 0.2–0.3s for large cards
6. **Duration**: 0.6s–1.2s for reveals, 0.3s for hover/interaction

### ScrollTrigger Defaults
```ts
scrollTrigger: {
  trigger: element,
  start: "top 80%",          // element top hits 80% of viewport
  toggleActions: "play none none none",
}
```

### Parallax Pattern
```tsx
useGSAP(() => {
  gsap.to(".parallax-slow", {
    y: -80,
    ease: "none",
    scrollTrigger: {
      trigger: sectionRef.current,
      start: "top bottom",
      end: "bottom top",
      scrub: 1.5,
    },
  })
}, { scope: sectionRef })
```

